I am an old, old man. I live in a bothy in a deep and relentless forest that is little visited. I now spendmost of my time looking at the trees, their shapes, and the sounds they make when moving and talking. I try not to survey what has brought me here, my previous life and loves, and the accumulation of small, distinct steps that didn't appear random at the time. My favourite moments are when the light starts to fade and lilac sunbeams orchestrate the tree-tops before dusk. I like the sound of these colours. This is my soundtrack.
